cs.CV, cs.GR, cs.HC, cs.MM, cs.RO

Reasoning: 
- cs.CV (Computer Vision) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on face alignment, head pose estimation, and facial attribute retrieval using computer vision techniques. 
- cs.GR (Graphics) is also likely as the paper discusses augmenting the faces of people seen through the HoloLens with various objects and animations. 
- cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction) is another possible category as the paper aims to improve human-to-human interactions through the use of augmented reality. 
- cs.MM (Multimedia) is a possible category as the paper deals with processing and analyzing multimedia data (i.e. images and videos) to extract facial attributes. 
- cs.RO (Robotics) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper discusses fitting a deformable 3D model to the landmarks localized using face alignment, which is a technique commonly used in robotics for object recognition and tracking.
